# Site integrity skill (pointer)

Canonical: [`/skills/site-integrity/SKILL.md`](../../skills/site-integrity/SKILL.md). Read it before acting.

Key points:

- **Read-only** — the skill reports findings only; fixes belong to the responsible content skill (page, faq, events, operational-facts, images, testimonials, rollback).
- Always start with a clean `npm test && npm run build` from `site/`. A stale `dist/` makes the audit meaningless.
- Eight dimensions: (1) internal link resolution, (2) external link health (HEAD-check opt-in), (3) locale parity, (4) canonical + hreflang, (5) registry coherence, (6) image reference integrity, (7) sitemap canonicalness, (8) redirect chain length.
- Rely on existing tests (`build-output-structure.test.ts`, `page-shell-registry.test.ts`, `url-matrix-parity.test.ts`, `chrome-navigation-resolve.test.ts`) for structural coverage; this skill catches drift between source modules and what actually ships in `dist/`.
- Berlin English story shells canonicalise to Stockholm English by design (per `BERLIN_EN_STORY_SEO_CANONICAL` + documented exceptions) — do not flag this as an error.
- External HEAD-checks are opt-in only; TripAdvisor and social domains block bots aggressively and will false-positive.
- Output a markdown report grouped by dimension, with `- none.` under clean dimensions (do not omit headings).
- Escalate: build failures (fix those first via page / rollback skills), shipped SEO regressions (needs SEO skill or Gustaf), intentional multi-hop redirects that pre-date the audit.
